trans-unit.source: Represents information about the route and virtual path that are the result of generating a URL with the ASP.NET routing framework.

When you generate a URL by using the ASP.NET routing framework, an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData> class is returned by the <xref:System.Web.Routing.RouteCollection.GetVirtualPath%2A> method.

The <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData> class contains information about the route that matched the values that you provided when you called the <xref:System.Web.Routing.RouteCollection.GetVirtualPath%2A> method.
The <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData> object also contains the generated URL in the <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData.VirtualPath%2A> property.
The <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData.DataTokens%2A> property contains custom values for the route.
You retrieve the route object that is used for generating the URL by using the <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData.Route%2A> property.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData"></xref> class.
The object that is used to generate the URL.
The generated URL.
Gets the collection of custom values for the route definition.

You use the <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData.DataTokens%2A> property to retrieve values that are associated with the route, but that are not used to determine whether a route matches a URL pattern.
These values can be used by the route handler to process the request.
A collection of custom values for a route.
Gets or sets the route that is used to create the URL.
An object that represents the route that matched the parameters that were used to generate a URL.
Gets or sets the URL that was created from the route definition.
To generate a URL, you call the <xref:System.Web.Routing.RouteCollection.GetVirtualPath%2A> method.
That method returns an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData> class, which contains information about the route.
The <xref:System.Web.Routing.VirtualPathData.VirtualPath%2A> property contains the generated URL.
The URL that was generated from a route.
